          "You had a good life, about to make partner just shy of 35 at your firm, when everything started falling apart. Your daughter developed some kind of mysterious wasting illness, whihc put enough of a strain on your marriage that your spouse started cheating on you. You had a retaliatory affair, but they turned out to be a raging psycho who revenge porn'd you to all your coworkers. You kept your job, but kiss being partner goodbye. Then the medical bils for your daughter meant you fell behind on the mortgage, but that didn't matter anyway when your spouse cleaned you out and moved to France. Sitting alone in a foreclosed house devoid of furniture or a future, you put serious thought into ending it all. Only two things stopped you: you weren't sure you had enough Xanax to actually get the job done, and your sire arrived. They gave you a whole new life - or unlife. However, while you were learning Path of Night, you made a horrible realization - everything that had happened to mortal you was your sire's direct fault! The wasting disease, the affair, the other affair - all perfectly done to break you down. You couldn't deal with your sire after that. You left, and found Rising Tide. They talk a good game about the Pander movement, and they're taking you to Joseph Pander so you can divest yourself of the last few things your sire gave you. But... you're still hesitant. You like being Lasombra. Even the dark parts, you're coming around to. But your pack has only your best interests at heart... right?"
